    <etym xml:lang="ru">Возводится к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                    ><lang/><w>*var-</w><gloss><q>желать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ira"><w/><gloss><q>выбирать</q></gloss></mentioned>, с необычным развитием
        начального %iv%i → %ib%i (cp., однако, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bar"/> ‘право’, ‘воля’,
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_byjyn"/> ‘вить’). Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>var-</w><gloss><q>выбирать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>предпочитать</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>var-</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w>vṛnoti</w><gloss><q>предпочитает</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>желает</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>любит</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="cu"
                ><lang/><w>вѣлети</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="cu"><w>воля</w></mentioned>, ,
            <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>велеть</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                ><w>воля</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="lt"
                    ><lang/><w>vêlyti</w><gloss><q>желать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="goh"><lang/><w>wellan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                ><lang/><w>wollen</w><gloss><q>желать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>volo</w><gloss><q>я хочу</q></gloss></mentioned>. Для объяснения
        осетинской формы приходится исходить из усиленной основы %ivarya%i--, в этом случае %ir%i
        перед %iу%i закономерно дал %il%i, а геминация %ily%i →%ill%i (как <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_allon"/> из %iāryana%i и др.); ср. основу %ivarya%i- в таких
        образованиях, как <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>varya-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>vairya-</w><gloss><q>желанный</q></gloss></mentioned>. В
        ближайшем родстве с %ibællyn%i стоят <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bar"/> ‘воля’, ‘право’ и
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bærgæ"/> ‘хотя’; в более отдаленном — <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_wyrnyn"/> ‘верить’.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>245</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                    ><lang/><w>*var-</w><gloss><q>wish</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ira"><w/><gloss><q>choose</q></gloss></mentioned>, with the unusual
        development of the initial %iv%i → %ib%i (cf., however, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bar"/>
        ‘right’, ‘will’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_byjyn"/> ‘wind’). Cf. <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>var-</w><gloss><q>choose</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>prefer</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>var-</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>vṛnoti</w><gloss><q>s/he
                    prefers</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>s/he
                    wishes</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>s/he
                    loves</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="cu"
            ><lang/><w>věleti</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="cu"><w>volya</w></mentioned>, ,
            <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>velet'</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                ><w>volya</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="lt"
                    ><lang/><w>vêlyti</w><gloss><q>wish</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="goh"><lang/><w>wellan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                ><lang/><w>wollen</w><gloss><q>wish</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>volo</w><gloss><q>I want</q></gloss></mentioned>. For explaining
        of the Ossetic form we have to start from a %bstrong%b stem %ivarya%i-; in this case %ir%i
        before %iу%i turned into a regular %il%i, and the gemination %ily%i →%ill%i (like <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_allon"/> derived from %iāryana%i etc.); cf. the stem %ivarya%i-
        in such derivations as: <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>varya-</w></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>vairya-</w><gloss><q>desired</q></gloss></mentioned>.
        The following words are close related to the word %ibællyn%i: <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_bar"/> ‘will’, ‘right’ and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bærgæ"/>
        ‘although’; in a less related word <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wyrnyn"/>
                ‘believe’.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
        /><biblScope>245</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
